14/05/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Parliament is to debate a measure Wednesday (14 May) authorising a military drill with US troops by the end of the year.
Lawmakers will also discuss a recommendation from the defence ministry for the participation of military observers in peace missions to India and Pakistan.
On Tuesday, Defence Minister Zeljka Antunovic met with her Slovak counterpart Ivan Simko to outline forms of military co-operation.
They announced possible joint peacekeeping operations in Cyprus and East Timor.
(Vecernji List, Vjesnik - 14/05/03;
HINA - 13/05/03)
